<taxonomicName id="4C714D228136FF9AFD23FE52FBBAFE2E" authority="(Thunb.) Rchb." authorityName="Rchb." baseAuthorityName="Thunb." box="[687,1033,482,509]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Bletilla" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="striata">
<emphasis id="B905EAB38136FF9AFD23FE52FCE1FE2E" box="[687,850,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Bletilla striata</emphasis>
(Thunb.) Rchb.
</taxonomicName>
f., but it differs in having the lip keels wavy throughout their entire length (not just on the midlobe). It is a variable entity and probably hybridises with 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D228136FF9AFA1FFDB7FEF1FD96" authority="Schltr." authorityName="Schltr." class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Acampe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ochracea">
<emphasis id="B905EAB38136FF9AFA1FFDB7FF43FD96" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">B. ochracea</emphasis>
Schltr.
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="F36676318136FF9AFEE5FD9AFE03FD96" box="[361,432,554,580]" name="China" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">China</collectingCountry>
. The specimens 
<emphasis id="B905EAB38136FF9AFDE1FD9BFC34FD96" box="[621,903,554,581]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Sue Koe 10037 &amp; 10092</emphasis>
identified in Kew as 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D228136FF9AFB0CFD9BFB59FD96" box="[1152,1258,555,580]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Bletilla" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="striata">
<emphasis id="B905EAB38136FF9AFB0CFD9BFB59FD96" box="[1152,1258,555,580]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">B. striata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
probably belong here.
</paragraph>
